rdf:resource="http://lod.bco-dmo.org/id/deployment/514193"/>     <odo:hasAcquisitionDescription rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#HTML"><div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" lang="en"><p>Wiebe's hand-written notes from MOCNESS ship log book regarding the tows.\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffd<br /> 8/8/03 NJC<br /> \ufffd\ufffd<br /> Ship speed ~2 knots for all tows<br /> Both \ufffd\ufffd" and 9-track tape-recorded all tows.<br /> \ufffd\ufffd<br /><strong>KN53 Nov. 1975\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffd</strong><br /> \ufffd\ufffd<br /> M23\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffdSargasso, shallow, day.\ufffd\ufffd Slight boble (sic?) at the surface flow meter pin broke - tried to bring net \ufffd\ufffd<br /> back to surface to pull pin out - ship's speed too slow, angle too low in setting net; got many spurious net \ufffd\ufffd<br /> responses (cycled from net 0 to net 15 back to 0 and then to net 3) Net 4 was really net 1.\ufffd\ufffd No net response \ufffd\ufffd<br /> fro net 3.\ufffd\ufffd Speed in about 10 m/min until we hit 60 m then increased speed of wire in to 13 m/min.\ufffd\ufffd Tow \ufffd\ufffd<br /> looks all right - good collections.\ufffd\ufffd We had special funnels in cod ends but some came loose.<br /> \ufffd\ufffd<br /> M24\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffdSargasso, deep, day.\ufffd\ufffd Lost flow counts in wind - reset at 50 counts for net 0.\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffd" tape turned on as \ufffd\ufffd<br /> net 0 coming up (810 m) just before opening net1.\ufffd\ufffd up at 25m/min.\ufffd\ufffd No net response for 'close 2/open 3' \ufffd\ufffd<br /> but angle showed nets were changed.\ufffd\ufffd No net response from 'close 3/open 4' but 'close 4/open 5' got a net \ufffd\ufffd<br /> response and 'close 5/open 6' ok. Net 7 close/8open - no net response.\ufffd\ufffd All samples look good - funnels in \ufffd\ufffd<br /> cod end seem to work very well - animals in very good shape.<br /> \ufffd\ufffd<br /> M25\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffdSargasso , deep, night.\ufffd\ufffd Not very good launch - 3 spurious net responses (NR) also had to set flow \ufffd\ufffd<br /> counter due to reverse in the wind.\ufffd\ufffd No NR for net 1 and therefore flow meter counter overflowed to show \ufffd\ufffd<br /> '$', however flow calculation ok.\ufffd\ufffd No NR for net 2.\ufffd\ufffd Net command has a bug in it - it resets itself even \ufffd\ufffd<br /> though there is no NR.\ufffd\ufffd This screws up the computer and it no longer prints out net count (NC) but does \ufffd\ufffd<br /> record ELCT errors.\ufffd\ufffd NR not working. - Very hard tow due to electrical malfunctions. - Samples look good.\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffd<br /> All nets seem to have opened and closed as expected.<br /> \ufffd\ufffd<br /> M26\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffdSargasso, shallow, night.\ufffd\ufffd No NR on net 6 close/net 7 open.\ufffd\ufffd No NR on net 8 close. Samples \ufffd\ufffd<br /> look good.<br /> \ufffd\ufffd<br /> M27\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffdRing, deep (800m), day.\ufffd\ufffd Down at 30m/min; up at 25 m/min.\ufffd\ufffd Very nice haul on slope water edge \ufffd\ufffd<br /> of ring core.\ufffd\ufffd No electrical errors<br /> \ufffd\ufffd<br /> M28\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffdRing, shallow (300m), day.\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffd" tape started at 1405 - just slightly after net in water.\ufffd\ufffd Wire out at \ufffd\ufffd<br /> 30m/min; in at ~15m/min.\ufffd\ufffd We are not sure that conductivity reading when net first in water is reliable - \ufffd\ufffd<br /> looks like 1st 25 m is bad.\ufffd\ufffd Also true on other records previous to this tow.\ufffd\ufffd Tow appeared perfect - no \ufffd\ufffd<br /> failures visible.<br /> \ufffd\ufffd<br /> M29\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffdRing, deep, night.\ufffd\ufffd When net at 640m (1500 meters of wire out, MWD), slip rings came off the \ufffd\ufffd<br /> winch and signal was cut.\ufffd\ufffd Winch halted until slip rings repaired.\ufffd\ufffd Time when failure occurred = 1909, \ufffd\ufffd<br /> thanks to Al Morton and Steve Boyd back to business at 1938.\ufffd\ufffd Resume paying out wire - while net 5 was \ufffd\ufffd<br /> open speed of net got up over 3 knots; so I had ship slow down but it was too much and net lost depth thus \ufffd\ufffd<br /> net 5 undulated in interval 400-300m.\ufffd\ufffd Beautiful catches.\ufffd\ufffd 1 large fish in bucket 4 to Margo for photophore \ufffd\ufffd<br /> removal from under eyes. \ufffd\ufffd<br /> \ufffd\ufffd<br /> M30\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffdRing, shallow, night.\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffd" tape on at 2246.\ufffd\ufffd We got a spurious NR during the set of net 0 - strange \ufffd\ufffd<br /> tow - net 2 started dropping and went back down to 191m with no change in ship's speed or winch hauling \ufffd\ufffd<br /> rate.\ufffd\ufffd Tow not good - no NR at all except 2 more spurious ones.\ufffd\ufffd Aborted tow.\ufffd\ufffd We had the motor \ufffd\ufffd<br /> unplugged thus no nets were tripped.\ufffd\ufffd Net 0 fished the entire time.\ufffd\ufffd All samples in cod-end buckets were \ufffd\ufffd<br /> washed and preserved to look at contamination.\ufffd\ufffd Most were almost entirely clean except net 8 which may \ufffd\ufffd<br /> have had material in the net from previous tow.<br /> \ufffd\ufffd<br /> M31\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffdRing, very deep, day: 0-1600m.\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffd" channel 1 down - off at 1031-1034 to rewind and switch \ufffd\ufffd<br /> channels to 2 while nets still going down and used channel 2 for apart of trace up - 0244 channel #3 when \ufffd\ufffd<br /> net started up.\ufffd\ufffd Had a lot of trouble with the line printer.\ufffd\ufffd Tom Crook spent a good portion of towing time \ufffd\ufffd<br /> with system shut down for repairs.\ufffd\ufffd Problem with wire going under ship stopped wire in at 1135.\ufffd\ufffd Start in \ufffd\ufffd<br /> again at 1152; depth of net ~1500.\ufffd\ufffd Net 2 fished from 1400 to 1500 m or deeper and then up to\ufffd\ufffd 1200m.\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffd" \ufffd\ufffd<br /> tape put on channel 2 tape 2 at 1348 or 459meters depth.\ufffd\ufffd Lost cod end bucket 4 - entire assembly came \ufffd\ufffd<br /> off.<br /> \ufffd\ufffd<br /> M32\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffdRing-D, shallow, night,.\ufffd\ufffd Very nice tow - no problems -\ufffd\ufffd good catches at center of ring.\ufffd\ufffd Note as in \ufffd\ufffd<br /> all past shallow and deep tows from about 100m to the surface samples had a lot of bioluminescent \ufffd\ufffd<br /> animals.\ufffd\ufffd I think they are jellies but I haven't been able to tell yet.<br /> \ufffd\ufffd<br /> M33\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffdRing, deep, night.\ufffd\ufffd One spurious NC going in.\ufffd\ufffd Weather rainy and windy, sea quite choppy.\ufffd\ufffd Out at \ufffd\ufffd<br /> 30m/min.<br /> \ufffd\ufffd<br /> M34\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffdRing high velocity core, deep, day.\ufffd\ufffd We got 1 spurious NR in setting nets into water.\ufffd\ufffd Sea very \ufffd\ufffd<br /> rough at launch and storm increased ferocity with winds increasing to 35 kts and seas building to over 15'.\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffd<br /> 1324-47-1/4" tape ran out of tape - rewind and then record on channel 2 on line(?) at =1327, 141m depth.<br /> \ufffd\ufffd<br /> M35\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffdSlope, deep, night.\ufffd\ufffd Started \ufffd\ufffd" tape at bottom of tow.\ufffd\ufffd 1944 slowed ship down. Wind freshening as \ufffd\ufffd<br /> storm approached.\ufffd\ufffd Slight overshoot on net 6 close/net 7 open.\ufffd\ufffd Very nice hauls.<br /> \ufffd\ufffd<br /> M36\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffdSlope, shallow, night.\ufffd\ufffd Forgot to turn on deck unit before going into aqui and before net was put in \ufffd\ufffd<br /> water.\ufffd\ufffd Net was at 203m before deck unit turned on .\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffd" tape turned on as net went into water.\ufffd\ufffd Net 8 \ufffd\ufffd<br /> opened on "2" commands.\ufffd\ufffd Very nice haul.\ufffd\ufffd All samples look good.\ufffd\ufffd No problems.\ufffd\ufffd All nets tripped and \ufffd\ufffd<br /> responded.<br /> \ufffd\ufffd<br /> M37\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffdSlope, deep, day.\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffd" taped started at ---.\ufffd\ufffd 9-track tape not turned on until 932-18.\ufffd\ufffd Possibly we did \ufffd\ufffd<br /> not get a header at beginning of tape.\ufffd\ufffd Had difficulty getting flowmeter pin out of flowmeter.\ufffd\ufffd We had to \ufffd\ufffd<br /> bring it back up to get the pin out.\ufffd\ufffd In so doing, we got a spurious NR.\ufffd\ufffd Printer paper advance \ufffd\ufffd<br /> malfunctioned for short time during Net 0.\ufffd\ufffd On this tow, because I forgot to put header on tape, we decided \ufffd\ufffd<br /> to SW15 EN at bottom of tow while net 0 still open and then begin a new file with a header before opening \ufffd\ufffd<br /> net 1 for start up.\ufffd\ufffd Thus far, MOCNESS 37 there are two files on the tape: one without a header for down \ufffd\ufffd<br /> trace, and one with a header for up trace.<br /> \ufffd\ufffd<br /> M38\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffdSlope, shallow, day.\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd" tape on at 1304 just after net in water, but I screwed up - wasn't on \ufffd\ufffd<br /> record.\ufffd\ufffd Start up after rewinding: time 1309-38.\ufffd\ufffd Good catches, good tow.<br /> \ufffd\ufffd<br /> M39\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffdSlope (warm-core ring edge?), deep, night.\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffd" tape started at bottom of tow.\ufffd\ufffd Very nice launch.\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffd<br /> Water here not really typical of slope - like a warm core ring.\ufffd\ufffd On start up of tow, pressure, temperature, \ufffd\ufffd<br /> and conductivity started dropping out intermittently.\ufffd\ufffd The rest of the parameters appeared to be OK.\ufffd\ufffd Good \ufffd\ufffd<br /> tow except for dropouts on CTP.\ufffd\ufffd One thing about samples to look at is very low biomass in net 5.\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffd<br /> Virtually none although everything appeared to have worked.\ufffd\ufffd Problem with CTD seems to have been with \ufffd\ufffd<br /> slip rings.\ufffd\ufffd After cleaning, signal on MOCNESS 40 very much improved and no signal dropouts.<br /> \ufffd\ufffd<br /> M40\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffdSlope (WCRing?), deep, day.\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffd" tape on channel 2 at 1052-44, ~820 m.\ufffd\ufffd This day sea was flat \ufffd\ufffd<br /> calm with only a few clouds and lots of bright sunshine.\ufffd\ufffd An incredible day for the last of November.\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffd<br /> Water here incredibly warm and salinity shows characteristics of Sargasso Sea.\ufffd\ufffd We found bucket 5 had a \ufffd\ufffd<br /> small hole in bottom edge of gauze and that organisms could be lost.\ufffd\ufffd This probably explains why catches \ufffd\ufffd<br /> between 400-300m (are low).\ufffd\ufffd Bucket changed.\ufffd\ufffd But must look at all previous tows on this cruise with some \ufffd\ufffd<br /> care. \ufffd\ufffd<br /> \ufffd\ufffd<br /> M41\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffdSlope, deep, night (at Hydrographer Canyon).\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffd" tape started at 1906.\ufffd\ufffd Slip rings are again giving \ufffd\ufffd<br /> static, at least CT &amp; P readouts are experiencing dropouts on way up.\ufffd\ufffd Also having problem with NR - only \ufffd\ufffd<br /> got 1 for net 1close/n2 open.\ufffd\ufffd Saw angle change for net 0 close/net1 open but hard to tell for net 2 close/net \ufffd\ufffd<br /> 3 open.\ufffd\ufffd Got no response for 4 close/5 open but saw angle change.\ufffd\ufffd Net 5 close/6 open gave response.\ufffd\ufffd Net \ufffd\ufffd<br /> 6 close/7 open gave response.\ufffd\ufffd Net 7 close/n8 open gave response.\ufffd\ufffd Samples all looked good.\ufffd\ufffd Sample 8 no \ufffd\ufffd<br /> formalin for 12-14 hours.<br /> \ufffd\ufffd<br /> M42\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffdSlope, deep, day (near Hydrographer Canyon).\ufffd\ufffd Sea quite rough and wind has been blowing steady \ufffd\ufffd<br /> 25-30 kts all night.\ufffd\ufffd Very nice launch; starting out depth of water ~800m.\ufffd\ufffd Kept net at surface for several \ufffd\ufffd<br /> minutes.\ufffd\ufffd 0816 - stopped winch 860m, 18 deg. angle.<br /> \ufffd\ufffd<br /> M43\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd \ufffd\ufffdSlope, horizontal at 350m, day.\ufffd\ufffd Started \ufffd\ufffd" tape at 1141.\ufffd\ufffd Net 1 open - long(?) horizontal but hard \ufffd\ufffd<br /> to keep net constant depth.\ufffd\ufffd Seems to be a good haul; all nets responded.</p> <p>\ufffd\ufffd</p></div></odo:hasAcquisitionDescription>     <dc:identifier
